{"questionId":"27727","questionHtml":"<p>Find an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use scalar product or formula for angle between two vectors&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">u</mi><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp; (seen anywhere)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mstyle><mo>+</mo><mi>sin</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><msqrt><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mstyle><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mstyle><mo>+</mo><mi>sin</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use an Argand diagram showing two complex numbers in the first quadrant with the angle between them marked as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>arg</mtext><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">u</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; (accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>arctan</mtext><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math>)&nbsp;<strong>and&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>arg</mtext><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27727","referenceCode":"22N.2.AHL.TZ0.7a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find an expression for cos θ in terms of n.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.12—Vector definitions","Topic 3